<div class="comments-head">Comments: I really wish more devs would make the switch</div>


<div class="comments-body">
<p>You know, I was one of the guilty ones with NewsGator until this last release.  <br />
I usually run with admin privileges (I know, I should stop), but I had a test VM in which I would test things as a non-admin user. Well, I thought everything was working fine, until I read a post a few days ago where Ted Neward and Craig Andera were commenting how things didn't work if you were non-admin.<br />
Heh...imagine my surprise when I realized my test VM didn't have a NTFS file system! Pretty much anything goes, no matter who you are, with FAT32.</p>
